prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: Hello dairy, my first surgery happened few weeks ago at the Central City hospital. if you must know, it was not a pleasant experience. As an IT personnel, After each work Day I usually located the nearest bar to relax and have a glass of drink. It all began one night, I was up due to a severe pain in my stomach. I took pain killers to ease the pain as I thought pain Killers would make me fine unfortunately the pain kept coming back. At first I thought I knew what was wrong with me. Drinks. I stopped taking all drinks except water. few days later, I started having the same trouble right in my Office. I wanted to come home First . Oh Gush! My stomach hurts. I held on to myself. security men noticed something was wrong with me as I walked out of the office building. I dont want to draw attention. "No one here needs to know what is going on with me" i thought as I dragged myself to the car. Can I drive? my hands were trembling. I knew I had to call for help or else I might loose myself. My phone, I started searching for my Phone. I wanted to call out for Help. that was when I passed Out! Yes! the next thing I remember was being on the Hospital bed. Surgery.

choices.text: I was in the theatre. The doctor told me I had to undergo a surgery. My appendix was about to burst. I was scared. I could not believe I had to undergo a surgery. I was too weak to even talk. the next thing I knew was waking up from the theatre. I was in pain. I was weak. I could not even talk. I was on the Hospital bed. I was scared. I did not know what was happening. I was alone. I was afraid. I was too weak to even call out for help. I was scared. I was alone. I wanted to go home. I did not want to be in the hospital. I wanted to be back to my normal self. I wanted to be back to my work. I wanted to be back to my drinks. I was scared. I was alone.
